narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I gained a good foundation in calculus of functions of several variables and learned more about the challenges of taking an online course.
I learned multivariate calculus.
Multi variable calculus; general problem solving techniques; attention to detail
I learned how to study better, and saw the rigor of Yale courses.

I learned how to manage my time a lot better due to the more intense workload and also learned to think critically about concepts in three dimensions. I think this course taught me how to truly apply what I learn and extend it to different ideas.
Multivariable calculus

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The strengths of this course were the instructor and the set up. I think one weakness was that the video lectures did not completely cover what was necessary for some of the problems.

Strengths: clear objectives, organized course, easy access to resources
Weaknesses: none
I thought the homeworks werent the best preparation for the exams. Longer, easier homeworks would have been helpful for this type of class.

This course was delivered very well and I was pretty pleased with it overall. I would have liked slightly more informative comments on some homework questions on Gradescope from my graders, but they usually gave detailed comments.

Accommodating and pleasant professor. Assignments, especially the exams, are very manageable, but the workload is high, and sometimes there were typos. Good structure that comes with all Math 120 classes. People did not participate much, unfortunately.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, if you like calculus and need to take Math 120 as a requirement.
Yes. It is a requirement for most majors.
Yes, good attention to detail and coverage of material

I think that this course was very helpful and well executed overall, and the professor Michele was very available and helpful during office hours as well as during class when answering questions from Zoom.
I would!

narratives.question_text: How will you use the knowledge and skills you learned in this course in your future endeavors?
comments: Calculus in 3D is very applicable to many different fields and I think this was a great foundation for future QR classes.
Multivariate calculus is useful for my major.

I will use the necessary time management and discipline that was required for this intensive course in my future classes, as well as in my occupation in the future. The ability to successfully allocate time and patience to this class material is very important and I plan on using this ability throughout my life.
